1
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:46,800
He used to say the river remembers
everything you throw into it.

2
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:19,100
[Rain on stone. Water moving.]

3
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:14,200
There are things that take years to reach you.
He left in November.

4
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:17,900
The grief arrived in March.

5
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:26,100
[Bridge. River swollen below.
Wind. A truck passes.]

6
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:49,800
I keep thinking I see him.
Not as a ghost. Just -- in the way

7
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:54,300
a room holds the shape of someone
who used to fill it.

8
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:33,700
[Group murmur. Rain outside.
Folding chairs.]

9
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:16,900
It's not that I want him back.
I know that's not possible.

10
00:06:17,100 --> 00:06:21,600
It's that I want to stop
being surprised that he's gone.

11
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:06,800
[River at night. Moonlight
on the water. Complete silence.]

12
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:49,100
I brought his photograph here every week
for three months.

13
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:53,800
Tonight I brought the box.
I don't know what that means yet.

14
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:19,200
[She does not throw it in.
She sits with it.]

15
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:06,900
[Spring. Morning light.
Tall grass. She walks.]

16
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:26,400
[She does not look back.]

17
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:47,800
[Silence. Then: birdsong.
Wind in the grass.]
